\boxed{Cherokee}

The **Cherokee Nation** negotiated the **Treaty of New Echota (1835)** with the U.S. government, which included provisions for the construction of the **Federal Road** (also known as the **Cherokee Mail Route**) to facilitate communication and trade. This road was part of broader efforts to integrate the Cherokee into U.S. infrastructure before their forced removal via the **Trail of Tears**.
